# .trivyignore
# CVEs reviewed and accepted as upstream risk in Ghost's node_modules.
# These cannot be fixed in the Dockerfile — they require Ghost to release
# updated dependencies. Re-evaluate each time Ghost releases a new version.
# Last reviewed: 2026-03-08

# @tryghost/members-csv — CSV injection during member export
# Risk: requires admin access to trigger; low exposure on personal blog
CVE-2024-34448

# axios — DoS via __proto__ key in mergeConfig
# Risk: internal Ghost usage only; not directly user-controlled input
CVE-2026-25639

# braces — DoS via unbounded string expansion
# Risk: build-time / internal tooling; not reachable via HTTP
CVE-2024-4068

# cross-spawn — ReDoS
# Risk: internal Ghost tooling only
CVE-2024-21538

# decode-uri-component — DoS via malformed input
# Risk: Ghost validates input upstream before reaching this
CVE-2022-38900

# form-data — unsafe random function
# Risk: used for internal multipart handling; not directly user-controlled
CVE-2025-7783

# glob — command injection via malicious filenames
# Risk: file operations are sandboxed to Ghost content dir
CVE-2025-64756

# http-cache-semantics — ReDoS
# Risk: affects caching layer; DoS only, no data exposure
CVE-2022-25881

# jsonwebtoken — unrestricted key type
# Risk: Ghost controls key generation; external JWTs are not accepted
CVE-2022-23539

# jws — HS256 signature verification bypass
# Risk: mitigated by Ghost's token validation layer
CVE-2025-65945

# knex — SQL injection in legacy query builder
# Risk: Ghost 6 uses a newer knex version for its own queries;
#       this instance is a transitive dependency
CVE-2016-20018

# luxon — ReDoS
# Risk: date parsing with attacker-controlled input is not a Ghost attack surface
CVE-2023-22467

# minimatch — ReDoS / catastrophic backtracking
CVE-2026-26996
CVE-2026-27903
CVE-2026-27904

# moment — ReDoS / path traversal in locale
# Risk: locale is set by Ghost config, not user input
CVE-2022-24785
CVE-2022-31129

# multer — DoS via dropped connections / malformed requests
# Risk: Ghost limits upload size; DoS requires sustained attack
CVE-2026-2359
CVE-2026-3304
CVE-2026-3520

# node-forge — ASN.1 recursion / interpretation conflict
# Risk: used for TLS cert handling; Ghost handles certs at the proxy layer
CVE-2025-12816
CVE-2025-66031

# nodemailer — DoS via crafted email header
# Risk: sender addresses are validated by Ghost before reaching nodemailer
CVE-2025-14874

# nth-check — ReDoS
CVE-2021-3803

# path-to-regexp — ReDoS
# Risk: route patterns are defined by Ghost, not user input
CVE-2024-45296

# semver — ReDoS
CVE-2022-25883

# systeminformation — arbitrary command execution via network interface param
# Risk: Ghost uses this for admin health stats; not user-controlled input
CVE-2026-26280
CVE-2026-26318

# tar / tar-fs — path traversal / symlink poisoning
# Risk: tar extraction only occurs during theme installation (admin-only)
CVE-2026-23745
CVE-2026-23950
CVE-2026-24842
CVE-2026-26960
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2024-12905
CVE-2025-48387
CVE-2025-59343

# trim — ReDoS
CVE-2020-7753

# underscore — arbitrary code execution via template / DoS
# Risk: template function is not exposed to user input in Ghost's use
CVE-2021-23358
CVE-2026-27601

# validator — incomplete filtering
# Risk: Ghost applies additional validation on top of this library
CVE-2025-12758

# gosu binary (Go stdlib) — crypto/tls, archive/tar, net/url, archive/zip
# Risk: gosu runs only at container startup for privilege dropping;
#       not reachable after boot. Requires Ghost Docker team to rebuild gosu.
CVE-2025-68121
CVE-2025-58183
CVE-2025-61726
CVE-2025-61728
CVE-2025-61729
